Bank of America Corp.  hired former
Morgan Stanley banker  Joaquin Arenas  as head of corporate and
investment banking for Spain and Portugal.  Arenas, 48, will be based in Madrid and start in May after
leaving  Morgan Stanley , where he started working in 1991, Bank
of America executives including  Alex Wilmot-Sitwell , president
of European and emerging markets excluding Asia, said in a memo
to employees. The contents of the memo were confirmed by a Bank
of America spokeswoman in London today.  Arenas replaces Ricardo Paz, who will continue to run sales
and trading in Iberia, Bank of America said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ambereen Choudhury in London at 
